<main class="container-fluid text-center my-4 p-4 w-75 shadow bg-white rounded d-flex justify-content-around">
    <div class="mx-2">
        <h1 class="text-center">With in-memory array</h1>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>GET /books</strong> - Retrieve all books</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>GET /books/:id</strong> - Return books with specific ID</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>POST /books</strong> - Create New Book with body</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>PUT /books/:id</strong> - Update current book with new data in body</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>DELETE /books/:id</strong> - Delete book by ID</p>
        <p class="fs-5">P.S.: After each update of Node.JS or my Render Website, the data in array will be destroyed</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mx-2">
        <h1 class="text-center">With MongoDB Atlas</h1>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>GET /books-mng</strong> - Retrieve all books</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>GET /books-mng/:id</strong> - Return books with specific ID</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>POST /books-mng</strong> - Create New Book with body</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>PUT /books-mng/:id</strong> - Update current book with new data in body</p>
        <p class="fs-4"><strong>DELETE /books-mng/:id</strong> - Delete book by ID</p>
